# Network Enumeration Lab

## Description

Performed network enumeration on a target machine to identify open ports and running services.

## Steps

* Ping failed (no ICMP response)
* Verified host using ARP
* Scanned with Nmap → port 80 open
* Detected nginx (Ubuntu)
* Tested HTTP with curl (200 OK)
* SSH connection refused
* Stopped nginx on target
* Verified service is down (no connection)

## Conclusion

The target was reachable despite no ping response, and the HTTP service was successfully identified and verified before being stopped.
